Merge pull request #57 from uzegonemad/feature/expose-request

Expose Mutable NSURLRequest

Fix designated initializer and allow subclassing

Because `-initWithURL:` is implemented by invoking `[self init]` instead of
calling up to `[super init]` and `-init` is not implemented here, it breaks
subclasses that choose for their designated initializer to be `-init`. When a
subclass that is designed to be initialized with a plain `-init` calls to super
to invoke `-initWithURL:`, `TOWebViewController` invokes `-init` on self causing
it to fallback into the subclass's implementation of `-init` causing an infinite
loop.
expose the request so it can be modified

Merge pull request #34 from plu/master

Add new option showDonebutton.

Add new option showDonebutton.

This adds a new option called showDoneButton. It defaults to YES, so no
change in behaviour for old code using TOWebViewController.

If you set this property to NO, it will not add a done bar button item
when presented modally. So it's up to the user where to place a button to
dismiss the view controller.

Set hideToolbarOnClose and hideNavBarOnClose once

Set hideToolbarOnClose and hideNavBarOnClose once

When a UIActivity presents a UIViewController,
such as UIActivityTypeMail, 
upon return viewWillAppear: will be called again
thus resetting hideToolbarOnClose and hideNavBarOnClose.
Avoid by setting them during viewDidLoad.

Merge pull request #8 from melsam/make-loading-url-optional

Make the URL optional when loading a page.

Added a showUrlWhileLoading BOOL property to prevent showing the URL while the page is loading.
I'm building an app where the initial URL is always redirected to something else (kind of like clicking on a bit.ly link). It is desirable to hide the initial URL in this scenario, since it is never the final URL.
Added explicit deprecation ignore flags for code that is only executed on pre-iOS 7 versions.
